        "content": "<p>Hello,<br>\nhow can i wirte a function in Lean that only is defined for two distinct input values like a (a:Nat) -&gt; (b:Nat) -&gt; Nat with the condition (a != b). I tried using an implicit argument for an assumption {not_equal: a != b}, but lean is not able to synthesize the implicit argument</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">fn</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">!=</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">}:=</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">#eval</span> <span class=\"n\">fn</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- should work without explicit proof</span>\n<span class=\"k\">#eval</span> <span class=\"n\">fn</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- this should not</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
